    .demo-description
      %p
        Because the accordion is comprised of block-level elements, by default its width fills the available horizontal space. To fill the vertical space allocated by its container, set the boolean
        %code
          fillSpace
        option to true, and the script will automatically set the dimensions of the accordion to the height of its parent container.  The accordion will also resize with its container if the container is
        %code
          resizable
        \.
